} 11. Bb5 $1 ({Calmer, without forcing events is} 11. Nd4 Qd5 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13.
Bxd7+ Kxd7 14. Qa4+ Ke7 15. O-O Qh5 16. h3 Rhd8 17. Rad1 Nd5 18. Bc1 Nb6 19.
Qc2 Kf8 20. c4 Be7 21. Nf3 $14 {With a slight white advantage.}) 11... Qxb5 12.
Qxd6 Qd7 13. Qa3 b5 {[%cal Ga3f8,Re8g8,Rh8f8]} 14. O-O Bb7 {[%cal Gb7f3]} 15.
Rad1 Qc7 16. Rfe1 {The first player allows the capture on f3 and concentrates
on finishing his development.} Bxf3 17. gxf3 Rc8 18. f4 $1 h5 19. Qb4 a6 20. f5
$36 {With a white initiative.}) 11. Bd4 Bb7 ({Also possible is} 11... Qc7 12.
Bc4 c5 13. Bxf6 gxf6 14. Qe2 Rb8 15. O-O-O Bb7 16. g3 O-O 17. Rhe1 Rfd8 18. Nd2
$14 {[%cal Gd2e4,Gc4d3,Gd3e4,Gd2c4] The first player tries to improve his
