, although it is not an easy decision to give up a pawn and go on the defence.}
18. Re1 Nd7 19. Bxe5 Bxe5 20. Nc4 O-O-O 21. Nxe5 Nxe5 22. Rxe5 Rd1+ 23. Re1 Rd2
$11) 18. Bxf6 gxf6 19. Ke2 Rg8 20. g3 O-O-O 21. Nc4 $14 {White has a stable
