11. Qa4 O-O 12. Nxc6 Bxe3 13. Ncd4 axb5 14. Qxa8 Bxd4 15. cxd4 $16) 11. Nxd4
Qc7 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Qf3 Nd5 14. Bc4 O-O (14... Nxe3 15. Qxe3 $14) 15. Bc5 Re8
16. O-O e5 17. Rfe1 Be6 18. Bf1 Nf6 19. c4 $14 {The bishop pair and better
pawn structure on the queenside guarantee a slight advantage for the first
player.}) 10. Bd3 Bd6 (10... Bc5 11. O-O Nxd4 12. cxd4 $1 {The white pieces
are well placed to transpose to an isolated pawn structure.} Be7 13. Ne5 Qd5 {
The best chances offered} (13... Qd8 $5) 14. Re1 (14. Bc4 Qd6 15. Bf4 Qd8 16.
Re1 O-O 17. Bg5 ({Somewhat better is} 17. Rc1 Bd7 18. Qf3 Bc6 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20.
