Bxa6 Qxb2 $11 {1/2-1/2 (36) Xie Jianjun (2417)-Xu, Y (2562) Changsha CHN 2019})
14... O-O 15. Rc1 Bd7 ({Dubious is} 15... b5 $6 16. Be2 $1 {[%csl Rd5][%cal
Ge2f3,Gf3a8]} Qd6 17. Bf4 Nd5 18. Bg3 Qd8 19. Nc6 Qd7 20. Bf3 {The pressure
increases.} Bg5 21. Rc5 Bb7 22. Bxd5 $1 exd5 23. Ne7+ Bxe7 24. Rc7 Qf5 25.
Rexe7 $36 {With an initiative.}) 16. Bc4 Qd6 {The black queen is exposed and
