while avoiding all issues with Nxc6 by White.} 12. Qc2 O-O ({Interesting is} 
12... h6 $5) 13. Bg5 Ng6 ({Most accurate is} 13... Qc7 14. Bxf6 $5 {
Considerably sharpening the position.} ({Other moves lead to calmer play.} 14.
c4 h6 15. Bxf6 gxf6 16. Rad1 Rd8 17. Qc1 Kg7 18. Ne2 Bd7 19. Ng3 Bxg3 20. hxg3
Rac8 $11) (14. Rfe1 Ned5 15. Rad1 h6 16. Bh4 b6 17. Bg3 Nf4 $11 {[%csl Gf4]})
14... gxf6 15. Bxh7+ Kg7 16. Bd3 Rh8 17. g3 Rh5 18. Rad1 e5 19. Nb3 Bh3 20.
