10... a5 11. Bb5 {The natural square for the light-squared bishop (sometimes
it moves to c4). Not only defending the white pawn on b4, but it can also be
useful for further simplifications.} Kd7 (11... axb4 {Before the exchange of
pawns, White can continue with} 12. Bxc6+ bxc6 13. cxb4 Nd5 14. Bd2 {[%csl Yb4,
Gd2][%cal Gd1c2,Gc2b3,Ga2a3,Gb1c3]} Be7 15. Kc2 f5 16. a3 Bf6 17. Nc3 $16) 12.
Kc2 Kc7 13. Bxc6 ({Another way to continue is} 13. Kb3 {An excellent square
for the white king.} Be7 14. a3 axb4 {Now, there is time to} 15. Bxc6 bxc6 16.
cxb4 Nd5 17. Nd2 Rhb8 18. Bb2 {[%csl Re5][%cal Gb2e5]} f6 {[%csl Rc5][%cal
Ge7c5]} 19. Kc2 $16 {[%cal Gd2c4,Gd2e4,Gh3h4,Gh1g1,Gg1g7] Reaching the type of
endgame that White wants.}) 13... Kxc6 ({After} 13... bxc6 14. a3 Nd5 {[%csl
Ra1][%cal Ga5b4,Gd5b4]} 15. Bb2 {[%cal Gb2a1] the a1-rook has to be defended
to support the queenside pawn structure.} f6 16. Nd2 Be7 17. Nc4 Rhb8 18. h4 ({
Also possible is} 18. Nxa5 Bxc5 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gc5f2]} 19. Rhf1 $16 {The
first player still has an advantage, but he unnecessarily allowed the
activation of the black bishop.}) 18... g6 19. h5 {[%csl Rg6] White's
advantage lies on the queenside, but that's no reason not to play all over the
board.} axb4 20. cxb4 Kd7 21. hxg6 hxg6 22. Rh6 $16 {[%csl Rg6]}) 14. Nd2 ({
More accurate is} 14. Kb3 Nd5 15. Rd1 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Ga2a4,Gb4b5] Black is
on the verge of being lost. He has no better option than a sad defensive
endgame after} axb4 16. cxb4 Nxb4 17. Kxb4 Bxc5+ 18. Kb3 Rhd8 19. Nc3 Bxf2 20.
Bb2 $16) 14... axb4 15. cxb4 Nd5 16. Kb3 {[%cal Ga2a4,Gc1b2,Gh1c1,Gb4b5]} b6 ({
More resistance offers} 16... b5 17. Bb2 f6 18. Ne4 Be7 19. Nc3 {Exchanging
the best black piece.} Rhd8 20. Rhd1 Ra7 21. Nxd5 Rxd5 22. Rxd5 Kxd5 23. a3 Ra4
24. Rd1+ $16) 17. a4 bxc5 ({There is no solution for the second player. The
only attempt can be} 17... Nxb4 18. Kxb4 Bxc5+ 19. Kb3 Bxf2 20. Ba3 $16) 18.
b5+ Kb7 19. Nc4 $18 {[%csl Gc4] With two passed pawns and a centralized knight,
White is winning.} Be7 20. Rd1 Rhd8 21. Bd2 {[%csl Ga5][%cal Gd2a5,Gc4a5]} Nb6
22. Na5+ Kc7 23. Nc6 Rd3+ 24. Kc2 Rxf3 25. Nxe7 Rxf2 26. a5 Nc4 27. Nd5+ Kb7
28. a6+ Ka7 29. Kc3 Nxd2 30. b6+ 1-0

