{Compared to structure I, here Black is the one with an extra pawn. This is
the main version of this queenless middlegame. The second player's main plan
is to advance the kingside pawns. White has two primary ideas. In the first
place, to activate the pieces in the center, or even the kingside, often
taking advantage of the exposed situation of the black king. Secondly,
activating the queenside pawns is another important priority.}  *

