{This structure is typicalfor Chapter XX. White can choose to castle on both
flanks. White's c-pawn can either advance to c4 or clear that square to place
a piece. When the second player wants to make a fianchetto with g6, White's
reaction with h4/h5 is often useful. The different positions that can be
reached are very rich in resources and variety of plans.}  *

