22. Rxd7 Bxg6 (22... Qxd7 $2 23. Qxf6 $18) 23. Rxc7 Bxf2 24. Rd1 $16) 18. Kb1
$16 ({An equally good move is} 18. cxd5 cxd5 19. Kb1 Rc8 20. Bc3 Bb6 21. h5 g5
(21... d4 22. hxg6 $1 $16) 22. Qe2 O-O (22... d4 $2 23. Bb5 $18) 23. Nxe5 $1 {
White returns a piece at the right time to destroy the black centre.} fxe5 24.
Qxe5 $16 {[%csl Rg5,Rg8][%cal Ge5g5,Ge5h8]}) 18... Rb8 19. h5 $1 {Ignoring the
black knight, the first player concentrates on progressing his attack on the
kingside.} Ne7 20. Bc3 $18 {[%csl Rd7,Rf2,Rg6][%cal Gd3g6,Gd1d7,Gc2f2]} Bf5 ({
