pieces.} 13. Na3 $14 Na5 14. Ne5 Bb7 15. Bg5 ({Somewhat more precise is} 15.
Rfe1 Rad8 16. Rad1 Bd5 17. b3 Qb7 18. Qf1 Nc6 19. Nac4 h6 20. Nxc6 Qxc6 21. Ne5
Qb6 22. Qe2 $14 {[%csl Gc4]}) 15... Rad8 16. Rad1 Ba8 (16... Bd5 17. Ng4 Nxg4
18. Bxe7 Qc7 19. Qxg4 Qxe7 20. b3 $14 {[%csl Gc4]}) 17. Rfe1 Nc6 ({The direct
threat} 17... Qb7 {[%cal Gb7g2] can be met with} 18. f3 {The kingside is
slightly weakened, but since the diagonal g1/b8 is blocked by the black pawn
on c5, this is not something serious.} Nc6 19. Nec4 Rd5 20. Bh4 Rfd8 21. Ne3
R5d7 22. Nac4 $14 {White continues to work with the strong c4-square for his
pieces.}) 18. Nac4 Qb7 19. Nxc6 Qxc6 20. f3 Qc7 21. Qe5 Qxe5 ({For Black, it
is preferable to avoid exchanging queens.} 21... Qb7 22. Bh4 h6 23. Qe2 $14)
22. Nxe5 $14 Rd5 23. Bc4 $1 {Facilitating the simplification of the position.
In the endgame, the weakness of the black c5-pawn will become more serious.}
Rxd1 24. Rxd1 $16 Rd8 $6 ({More tenacious is} 24... Rb8 25. b3 Bb7 26. Bh4 h6
27. Nd7 Nxd7 28. Bxe7 Nb6 29. Bd3 Rc8 30. c4 $16 {[%csl Rc5]}) 25. Rxd8+ Bxd8 {
[%csl Rc5]} 26. Nd3 ({More exact is} 26. Be3 $1 Bb6 27. Bb5 {[%csl Rc5][%cal
Rf6d7,Ge5d3,Ge3c5,Gd3c5]} Nd5 28. Bf2 $16 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Ge5d7,Gd7c5,Gf2c5]})
26... Bb6 ({Greater resistance could be offered with} 26... Bc6 27. Nxc5 ({
Probably the best.} 27. Ba6 $5 Be7 28. Ne5 Ba4 29. b3 h6 30. Bh4 Be8 31. Nd3
Bc6 32. c4 Bd6 33. Bc8 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Rf6d7,Gh4f2,Gf2c5,Gd3c5]} e5 34. Bg3
$16 {[%csl Rc5,Re5]}) 27... Bb6 28. Be3 Nd7 29. b4 Nxc5 30. Bxc5 Bxc5+ 31. bxc5
{White has an advantage, but the outcome of the endgame is uncertain.}) 27. Be3
Nd7 28. Bb5 c4 29. Kf2 cxd3 30. Bxd7 d2 31. Ba4 $16 {Tiviakov has everything
under control and has a clear advantage.} Bd5 32. Bxb6 ({Another way to
continue is} 32. a3 f5 33. Ke2 Kf7 34. g3 e5 35. Bxb6 axb6 36. f4 h6 37. Kxd2
exf4 38. gxf4 g5 39. Ke3 Bb7 40. Bd7 $16) 32... axb6 33. a3 e5 (33... g5 $5)
34. Ke3 Kf8 35. Bc2 f5 36. Kxd2 g6 37. h4 ({IPreferable is} 37. b4 $5) 37...
Ke7 38. Bd3 Kf6 39. c4 Bc6 40. b4 h6 41. b5 $1 {The Russian player
demonstrates his excellent technique.} Bb7 42. a4 Ke7 43. c5 $1 $18 bxc5 44. a5
Kd6 (44... e4 45. fxe4 fxe4 (45... Bxe4 $4 46. Bxe4 fxe4 47. Ke3 $18) 46. Bc2
c4 47. Ke3 c3 48. a6 Bd5 49. a7 $18 {[%csl Rc3][%cal Ge3d4,Gd4c3]}) 45. Bc4 Bc8
46. b6 Kc6 47. Kd3 g5 48. h5 {Black is in zugzwang and resigned.} Bd7 (48...
Bb7 49. a6 $18) 49. Bd5+ $1 $18 1-0

