Rh7,Rh8] White is better due to his more active pieces and Black's weaknesses.}
) 26. Rxe6 $1 Rxd4 (26... fxe6 27. Nxe6+ Rxe6 28. Rxd8+ Ke7 29. Rh8 Rf6+ 30.
Ke3 Rf7 31. h4 $16 {With a healthy extra pawn.}) 27. Rxd4 Rxd4 28. cxd4 fxe6
29. Ke3 Bd5 ({No better is} 29... g5 30. Bxh7 Bd5 31. a3 Ke7 32. Be4 $16 {
